node.text:
According to Bloomberg’s Mark Gurman, Apple will launch a new Mac mini in “the next several months” with a new design and more ports to replace the Intel Mac mini. This new Mac mini is expected to be high-end and feature Apple’s next-gen chip the M1X or M2 chip. Render from @rendersbyian

node.text:

node.text:
As part of the ongoing legal battle between Apple and Epic Games, an email from Steve Jobs in 2010 has revealed that Apple was considering making an “iPhone nano,” which would have been a miniature version of an iPhone 4. Jobs also mentioned he wanted to create a “low-cost ‌iPhone‌ model based on iPod touch to replace 3GS." Concept from @atuos_user

#Apple #iPhone4 #SteveJobs #iPhonenano #iPhone12 #iPhone13 #Tech #AppleHub

node.text:
According to Wedbush analyst Daniel Ives, the upcoming iPhone 13 lineup, likely the iPhone 13 Pro models will have a 1TB storage option. Ives also claims the new iPhone models will launch in the third week of September, which would make September 17 the likely release date. Ives also reaffirms that all models will feature a LiDAR sensor, a feature that is currently exclusive to the Pro models. Render from @rendersbyian
